File: 3,502 people have died as a result of COVID-19. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa's COVID-19 infections have risen by 9,063 in the last 24 hours. The death toll has increased by 108. The country's coronavirus related fatalities now stand at 2,952. The deaths are from the Northern Cape (3), Eastern Cape (8), North West (29), KwaZulu Natal (10) and from Western Cape (58). READ: US reports 55,000 COVID-19 cases in single day, hits new global record South Africa has 177,124 reported COVID-19 cases to date. 86 298 people have recovered which translates to a recovery rate of 48,7-percent. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.